Taiwan Equity Movers: HTC Corp., Nanya Technology Corp.

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-09-07T05:46:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-07/formosa-petrochemical-htc-nanya-tech-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 1:30 p.m. close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index rose 161.82 points, or 2.2 percent, to
7,529.01.  HTC Corp. (2498)  (2498 TT) surged 6.9 percent to NT$757, the
biggest advance since Nov. 1. The smartphone maker said August
sales surged 89 percent from a year earlier to NT$44 billion
($1.51 billion), according to a statement to the  Taiwan Stock
Exchange .  Nanya Technology Corp. (2408)  (2408 TT) lost 3.8 percent to
NT$3.81, the lowest close since Aug. 22. Elpida Memory Inc. said
it filed a patent lawsuit against Nanya at a California court.
Tokyo-based Elpida said in a press release that Nanya violated
patents on dynamic random access memory technology.  Nanya is “in the process of understanding” the patent
infringement lawsuit brought by Elpida in the U.S. and hasn’t
yet received the complaint from the court, the Taoyuan, Taiwan-
based memory-chipmaker said in a statement today. The case has
no material impact on Nanya Technology’s current operations, it
said in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
